         <abstract>
            <p>LIMITATIONS on manual steering when used in heavy-duty vehicles have led to the development of power steering. When power steering gears are used, there are certain characteristics of the manual systems that should be retained. These and other engineering requirements are discussed by Mr. Davis, along with an evaluation of the various power steering systems that have been developed, particular attention being given to the hydraulic type.</p>
         </abstract>
